VThe Fest: Parking advisory
p3
sVnews
p4
VPlease take note of the parking arrangements forThe HinduNovember Fest, which begins on November 10.Patrons are requested to adhere to the following arrangements:Only owner driven cars will be allowed to park at The Music Academy. Parking spaces are available on a first-come first-served basis. Since parking at The Academy is limited, use the space available at St. Ebba's School on Dr. Radhakrishnan Salai. Chauffeur-driven cars are requested to proceed to St. Ebba's School after the patron has alighted at the venue.A courtesy car service will be available at St. Ebba's to allow people there to be ferried to The Music Academy. A similar arrangement will be made available at the end of the programme at The Music Academy. Patrons are advised that there may be some delays in the return drop service to St. Ebbas as a result of the volume of cars leaving The Academy.For ticketsLimited tickets for the concert of Farida Khanum on November 10 available only at the Music Academy from 10 a.m. Tickets for other shows available only atLandmark, Nungam-bakkam.Bottom Template Starts
